25|$|An {{aircraft}} registration {{is a unique}} alphanumeric string that identifies a civil aircraft, in similar fashion to a licence plate on an automobile. In accordance with the Convention on International Civil Aviation all aircraft must be registered with a <b>national</b> <b>aviation</b> <b>authority</b> and they must carry proof of this registration {{in the form of}} a legal document called a Certificate of Registration at all times when in operation.|$|E
25|$|An {{aircraft}} registration {{is a unique}} alphanumeric string that identifies a civil aircraft, in similar fashion to a number plate on a vehicle. The letter Q has not been used since the issue of G-EBTQ in 1927 (although a few historic aircraft still maintain registrations with this letter), and the CAA also disallows combinations that may be offensive. In accordance with the Convention on International Civil Aviation all aircraft must be registered with a <b>national</b> <b>aviation</b> <b>authority</b> and they must carry proof of this registration {{in the form of}} a legal document called a Certificate of Registration at all times when in operation.|$|E
